      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "Update: I attempted this but had an [issue with libevent](https://github.com/libevent/libevent/issues/1615). There is a patch on libevent master now but looks like they don't ship releases any more, and outside of depends builds, we can't guarantee the user has the patched version installed. I'm not even sure how we update our depends builds to pull libevent master branch instead of a release.\r\n\r\nThere seems to be some [core dev support ](https://www.erisian.com.au/bitcoin-core-dev/log-2024-04-18.html#l-198) for replacing libevent entirely, and so I am working on that.\r\n\r\nThe plan is to implement our own HTTP server using our cross-platform socket handlers in `netbase.cpp` and then write a loop similar to `ThreadSocketHandler` in `CConnman` to handle connections.",
